Map in collections:
import java.util.map:


Methods of Map:

put(), get(), size(), replace(), remove(),
containsKey(),containsValue(), isEmpty(),
equals(), clear(), keySet(),values(), entrySet()

   -- Collection of pair
   --Data structure based on Key +value pairs
   --Does not have IS A relation with Collection
   --Size can be increased or decreased (dynamic size)
   --Key CAN NOT be duplicated

   (to add elements has put())

HashMap class:
       --Implements the Map interface
       --Maintains the random order
       --Accept null value as a key
       --

LinkedHashMap class:
    --child class of hashMap
    --Maintains insertion order
    --Accepts null value as a key

TreeMap class:
    --Implements the sortedMap Interface
    --Maintains the sorted(Ascending) order (sorting keys in order)
    --Does NOT accept null as a key

HashTable Class:
    --Implements the map interface
    --Maintains the random order
    --Does not accept null as a key
    --Synchronized(Thread-safe)


    HashMap      vs     LinkedHashMap       vs      HashTable        vs      TreeMap


   HasMap               LinkedHashMap                 HashTable              TreeMap

   Not Synchronized      Not Synchronized            Synchronized            Not Synchronized

   allows one null key    allows one null key        does not allows any     does not allows any
   and multiple null      and multiple null          null key or value        null key or value
   values                  values

   random order           insertion order                 random order        Maintains sorted order
























